OL,3,CStarmer hints controversial two-child
OL,4,Cbenefit cap will be axed in Budget
OL,6,FThe two-child benefit cap was
OL,7,Fintroduced in 2015 by the
OL,8,FConservatives and came into effect in
OL,9,F2017. It restricts the child tax
OL,10,Fcredit and universal credit (UC) to
OL,11,Fthe first two children in most
OL,12,Fhouseholds.
OL,14,FIt is estimated that scrapping the cap
OL,15,Fcould lift 350,000 children out of
OL,16,Fpoverty and reduce the depth of
OL,17,Fpoverty for a further 800,000
OL,18,Fchildren, at a cost of more than #3bn.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
