OL,3,CStarmer hints controversial two-child
OL,4,Cbenefit cap will be axed in Budget
OL,6,FA child is said to be living in
OL,7,Fpoverty if they live in a household
OL,8,Fwith an income below 60% of the
OL,9,Fnational median income.
OL,11,FMany Labour backbenchers have been
OL,12,Fcalling for the cap to be scrapped
OL,13,Fsince Labour won the election in July
OL,14,F2024, after the party promised in the
OL,15,Fmanifesto that it would "develop an
OL,16,Fambitious strategy to reduce child
OL,17,Fpoverty".
OL,19,FBut Starmer suspended seven Labour MPs
OL,20,Flast year after they voted for an SNP
OL,21,Fmotion calling for an end to the cap.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
