OL,3,CStarmer hints controversial two-child
OL,4,Cbenefit cap will be axed in Budget
OL,6,FAlongside calling for the two-child
OL,7,Fcap to be scrapped, child poverty
OL,8,Fcharities are also urging the
OL,9,Fgovernment to scrap the overall
OL,10,Fhousehold limit on benefits.
OL,12,FIf the two-child cap is lifted, the
OL,13,FInstitute for Fiscal Studies estimates
OL,14,Fsome 70,000 of the poorest households
OL,15,Fwould then be pushed above the overall
OL,16,Fbenefit cap, meaning the gains from
OL,17,Freversing the two-child limit would be
OL,18,Ffully or partially wiped out.
